				<td colspan="2"><span>So monks will Lull now, Bards will no longer be able to Lull pull worth a crap, a few useful AA that worked as intended are being removed, a useless broken AA is being castrated and forced on us rather than being refunded like it should.  We already could not reliably Lull pull in Hard Dungeons and now we will always train the group if we bother to attempt it at all since it could drop at any time if it even works at all.   That is a really great way to screw over yet another class to &quot;fix&quot; it.  I guess that EQ2 must really be getting close for them to feel the need to drive off more players like this.  What the h*ll kind of testing did you do before coming up with this brain-child of an idea to where you can try to say that this is a good thing.  I agree that we need to have a lot longer Lull than 18 seconds for it to still be remotely useful and drop the resists sown to virtually nothing.  Also, if we are going to have to Fade a h*ll OF A LOT MORE due to crappy lulls, then allow us to regen mana like other classes... give us a med skill of 200, allow the Mana regen spells to work on us, drop the mana needed for Fading Memories down to like 150 or something else bards will once again be in the back of the line for any type of group ever.  I really have no desire to only be &quot;useful&quot; as a class for mana and resists on raids again.  If it comes to that, EQ and Sony can go screw themselves.  Things like this really make me wish World of Warcraft was closer to release.
<br />
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121585</span></td>
