				<td colspan="2"><span>If you read the message, the Lull change is NOT a nerf, it is a FIX.  We were broken, bards were never intented by design to have a lull that lasts that long.  I only see three possible problems this might pose for me.
<br />
#1  Caster mobs could pose a problem, as they might aggro mobs if they stand and try to nuke me for longer then 18 seconds.  
<br />
#2  Moving a group through mobs to get to a named or certain area is going to take a little more attention by the rest of the group.  
<br />
#3  Pulling a named or certain mob to my group through multiple rooms or areas will not be possible any more.  No more pulling Tables named to Deep south.
<br />

<br />
Just because we have become accustomed to playing a certain way does not mean it is wrong to fix it if it is out of balance.  And yes, bards were far and away the best pullers in a lot of situations.  Guess what though...
<br />
After this nerf, I will STILL be the best puller for most situations.  
<br />
This may force us to adjust a little bit, but with Fade, Gate song, Pacify, Long range low aggro pulling AAs or song, HP/AC to take a few hits while fixing a pull gone bad, and our ability to CC our own mess, talented bards will still be the choice to pull in most areas and situations.
<br />

<br />
As for the AE DOT nerf, I have never AE DOTd for exp, so this doesnt affect me in any way unless it affect the range of HoS or RoT.  If it does, then I will just use Bellow AA to pull long range stuff, no sweat off my sack.
<br />
For you bards that were getting multiple AA per hour AE kiting the planes, I hope you dont think that it is good for one class to have the ability to get exp so much faster then every other class.  It's all about balance, and getting exp that fast is not balanced at all.
<br />

<br />
Bards still kick a$ after this change, we are still the most versatile class in everquest, and we still have the ability to solo if we want, while remaining very sought after for groups.
<br />

<br />
Adjust and move on bards, both these changes fix or correct seriously out of balance abilities.  
<br />

<br />
And Sin, I know you are a better bard than that.  You, a useless group member?  Come on man, this is a small change to ONE of our roles in a group.</span></td>
