<br />

<br />
I must say that the one good thing in this potential nerf, is that my LDoN missions will go faster because I will be unable to lull an entire room before pulling a mob just to be safe.  It will be lull next closest, pull closest and pray for the best.
<br />

<br />
Also, though I don't have FM yet, (3.7 of the 6 needed saved up) unless you pull mobs from a few rooms away in LDoN, I don't see how it will help you, by the time you realize you have an add and fade, the mobs are in proximity range to aggro your group.  I'm sure it's just my inexperience with FM here, but I see FM for more of a BoT zone for pulling, etc.  /shrug
<br />

<br />
Let me say that in general I agree with you Sapper, but to call this anything but a knee-jerk reaction and a nerf is IMO wrong.  I wouldn't mind, as stated on tCH, if lull was trimmed to 7 ticks just like chanter/cleric/and now MONK lulls.  Of course I have never had any idea how long our lull lasted, so I re-lull every pull that's needed.
<br />

<br />
If you don't agree with me, fine, I'm cool with that.  I just won't ever call taking an ability like lulling away from us a fix(effectively that's what they're doing if Thott is correct, and I hope he is not).  I'll end with this... to each his own...
