				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Wonderful upcoming changes...<a name="13271"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 15 03 1:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sapper,
<br />

<br />
Your arguments are all fine and good for the bards that are 56+ (for Highsun) and 63+ (for FM).  Sure we can paci, but 18 secs is a very short time and will effectively negate its use in many situations.  So, that leaves us with being CC and manabatteries once again.  Now, I understand that is not all we are capable of, but the problem isn't in how well we know our class, but in how other classes perceive us.  With these changes, the lower level bards are hurt.  Also, go read the full thread on tCH to see that being vocal about these nerfs is what needs to be done.  Due to all of the posts about them, Rytan has reevaluated his position on Jamfest being &quot;fixed&quot; to not include resist songs.  And, the test server is now reporting that lull has a 5 tick duration.  Hopefully, that will make it live, but our lull really should have a 7 tick duration to match other classes.  At least something good has come out of this.
<br />

<br />
I play a bard extremely well (to Jackstraw), but my getting *invited* to a group depends on others perceptions.  I have to get invited first in order to teach the group what a bard is capable of, if they don't already know.  If I am getting invited to groups right now because they want me for pulling, then great.  That gives me an opportunity to show them what I can do in addition to pulling.  If the invites stop coming because they would rather have a monk and an enchanter instead, then I HAVE BEEN NERFED.  The net result of these nerfs is that it will make it harder to find a group.  Yes, I will still be a valuable addition if they will take me, and yes, I can still go solo, but to say that we are not being nerfed is ridiculous if you take the time to read ALL of the changes.
<br />

<br />
Rhapsodde Enbleu
<br />
