				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Wonderful upcoming changes...<a name="13321"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 16 03 10:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My 2cp worth:
<br />

<br />
I think that any bugs that have not been identified and fixed for a long period - say 2 releases are condoned.  SOE has to be accountable for their product.  That said a nerf only means you can shout NERF in posts and flames.
<br />

<br />
I also dont think that the change to lull is out of line with what bards are supposed to be capable of.  We can melee, charm, mez, buff, haste, slow etc.  But none of it except for buffing is as good as other ability classes of our level.  Why then should be be able to lull mobs for longer than others or even as long as others?  I agree 18 seconds is very short, but if you need to lull more then that is what the rest of your group is for - it is actually a team game and we support the team.  It is not the end of the world for Bards, it is just a change.
<br />

<br />
Tin.</span></td>
